stimulus: Welcome to the Massive Memory Experiment. Press any key to move on.

In the first section you will see a stream of images, with fixation crosses in between each image.

Each image will remain on screen for 2 seconds. Your job is to detect images that you have seen before within the experiment. Whenever you see an image that you have seen previously at any point in the stream of images, press the spacebar.

We will let you know if you have correctly or falsely clicked the spacebar on an image by changing the color of the fixation cross.

If you press the spacebar correctly (the image really did appear earlier), the fixation cross will turn green. If you pressed the spacebar incorrectly, the fixation cross will turn red.

Please watch carefully to detect the images that show up again!

Press any key to start.

In the next part of this experiment, you will see 2 images. Please select the image that you recall from the image stream.

You will also rate your confidence for each image you recall.

Press any key to start.
